house speaker tom foley knows his way around 
the power corridors of the nations capital its finding his new 
office that occasionally has him doing an aboutface 
old habits die hard said foley admitting that he 
occasionally leaves the house floor and finds himself heading down 
the stairs toward his old office 
for eight years first as democratic whip and then as majority 
leader the cozy suite on the ground floor in the original part of 
the capitol building was home to foley his staff and his aging dog 
alice 
tourists wandering the main hallway would often peek inside 
trying to catch a glimpse of someone famous when mice were 
discovered scampering about foley brought in a cat 
