pell aides say the senators lack of fundraising is merely an 
outgrowth of his concern that the campaign season has become too 
long 
he has said repeatedly he has every intention of running 
said a senior pell aide who spoke on the condition of anonymity 
he just feels very strongly that the campaign process has gotten 
out of hand 
pell does have 444686 in his campaign coffers in preparation 
for 1990 but 21 of the 30 other senators running next year have 
more according to fec documents 
pell is one of the most popular politicians in rhode island 
history winning his senate seat in 1960 by defeating two former 
governors in a primary he has been a leading advocate for the arts 
and education and in 1986 became chairman of the powerful foreign 
relations committee 
but chairmen of that committee have in the past have suffered at 
reelection time attacked by challengers who charge they are 
paying too much attention to international problems and not enough 
to parochial concerns five years ago democrat paul simon unseated 
thenforeign relations chairman charles percy rill 
miss schneider has statewide recognition since rhode island has 
only two house seats and she is the type of republican that 
democraticdominated rhode island likes a liberal on social 
issues with a strong environmental record 
age also could become a factor miss schneider is 42 the same 
age pell was when he first came to the senate nearly 30 years ago 
pell will be 71 in november and would be 78 at the end of 
another sixyear term 
pell however would still be a youngster compared to his 
predecessor theodore green came to the senate at age 69 and 
retired in 1960 at age 93 
