flawless 
a news blackout ordered by the department of defense prevailed 
over the flight and only a few brief announcements broke the 
silence even the landing was closed to the public 
the main goal of the mission was widely believed to be 
deployment of a powerful 10ton spy satellite that can snap highly 
detailed photographs of military installations troop movements and 
other targets around the world such a satellite would help the 
united states verify soviet compliance with arms treaties 
air force secretary donald rice confirmed last week that the 
