relief bill enacted during last years drought it will help farmers 
still facing parched fields in parts of the great plans and western 
corn belt as well as farmers in parts of the south where flooding 
wiped out rice and cotton crops 
to qualify for relief farmers in the government subsidy program 
for corn wheat cotton tobacco peanuts and sugar must suffer a 40 
percent crop loss the threshold will be 45 percent for soybean and 
sunflower growers and 50 percent for fruit and vegetable farmers 
