democratic star a pair of comeback minded exgovernors a 
millionaire oilman and rancher a democratturnedrepublican and 
corporate raider t boone pickens 
but it doesnt include president bushs eldest son george w 
bush of dallas coowner of the texas rangers baseball team 
although many republicans said he would be the frontrunner bush 
bowed out aug 1 saying the only race he cares about is for the 
american league pennant 
clements the states only republican governor this century had 
announced shortly after winning his second term that he didnt 
intend to seek a third hell be 73 when the term expires in january 
1991 the last incumbent to voluntarily step down was john connally 
in 1968 
in the wake of republican inroads in texas democratic national 
chairman ron brown recently said the state is crucial to party hopes 
for the 1990s he noted that no democrat has been elected president 
this century without carrying texas and added we have got to 
recapture the statehouse here 
but thats a costly proposition in a state that spans two time 
zones and has more than 20 television markets the 1986 race for 
example saw combined spending by clements and thengov mark white 
of about 25 million though both had little opposition 
while the primary isnt until march 1990 candidates in both 
parties have been jockeying for months only three have formally 
declared but a fourth is ready to do so tuesday and others are 
raising money or admit to considering a race 
state treasurer ann richards is the only announced democratic 
candidate she became an instant celebrity after her 1988 democratic 
national convention keynote speech accusing president bush of being 
born with a silver foot in his mouth she has banked more than 
1 million and favors abortion rights and more action to help the 
environment 
three other democrats are considering a run 
mattox except for his first try for party precinct chairman 
he has never lost a race for public office the former congressman 
compiled an activist record on consumer fraud nursing home abuse 
and environmental issues 
white he ousted clements in 1982 only to be ousted in return 
in 1986 now a lawyer in houston white says hell decide by fall 
whether to try a clementsstyle comeback 
dolph briscoe who was elected governor in 1972 and lost the 
democratic primary in 1978 the 65yearold multimillionaire rancher 
and banker says there is a vacuum of conservative leadership in the 
party 
there are two announced republican candidates and a third set to 
make his formal announcement this week 
clayton williams oilman rancher telephone company founder 
who pledged to spend 3 million of his own to win the republican 
nomination but his start was a little rocky when news reports noted 
that williams contributed to two democratic potential rivals mattox 
and ms richards last year 
rains he was campaign strategist for clements who appointed 
him secretary of state the states top political patronage job in 
1987 he quit the post when he launched his gubernatorial bid 
kent hance who is planning his formal announcement tuesday a 
onetime democratic congressman from lubbock he lost the 1984 
democratic nomination for senate then changed parties his 1986 bid 
for governor failed but he has since become a member of the 
powerful railroad commission which regulates oil and gas production 
in addition oilman pickens who has staged takeover battles of 
such wellknown companies as phillips petroleum is reportedly 
looking for a new house in dallas republican strongholds and has 
said he will decide soon whether to seek a different type of chief 
executives chair 
