<TEXT>
west germany closed its embassy and 
consulate monday to hundreds of east germans trying reach the west 
through hungary whose liberal refugee and border policies have 
angered some east bloc allies 
officials of the three nations conferred in an attempt to ease 
friction 
on sunday the west german foreign ministry said the embassy and 
consulate would be closed indefinitely beginning monday because the 
staff could not deal with so many people 
hungary has removed the barbed wire and other obstacles from its 
border with austria and east germans are pouring out of their 
strict communist nation which has rejected the political and 
economic reform popular elsewhere in the soviet bloc 
tens of thousands of politically and economically disgruntled 
east germans have gone to west germany this year the largest flow 
to the west since the berlin wall was built in august 1961 to stem a 
similar tide 
dozens of east germans who spent the night outside the west 
german consulate in budapest in cars or sleeping bags were joined by 
scores more on monday despite a sign announcing the closure 
more than 100 had gathered by midafternoon when hungarian red 
cross volunteers arrived with sandwiches and cold drinks 
the embassy and the consulate are temporarily closed said a 
sign handwritten in red letters on the consulate gate in an 
exclusive neighborhood on the buda side of the danube river a 
similar sign was posted on the wroughtiron embassy fence on the 
pest side 
officials in bonn said 181 east germans were inside the embassy 
when the gates were closed and more than 100 soon gathered outside 
at least 1600 east germans are estimated to have crossed 
illegally from hungary to austria since may when this liberal 
soviet bloc nation began dismantling the barriers on its western 
frontier 
in vienna they go to the west germany embassy for documents 
needed to enter that country sources said at least 200 east germans 
arrived at the embassy over the weekend which was the 28th 
anniversary of the berlin wall 
hundreds of others did not make it across the border the daily 
esti hirlap quoted interior ministry officials as saying hungarian 
border guards caught and temporarily detained 471 east germans 
during the weekend 
hungary with a relative abundance of consumer goods and vacation 
spots has been popular with east germans who have difficulty 
traveling legally to the west 
more than 1 million east germans have visited hungary in each of 
the last several years and this year the level has been running 
about 15 percent higher the interior ministry said 
east germans who feared authorities at home were told of their 
attempts to emigrate illegally started going to the west german 
embassy last month many want guarantees of safe passage to the west 
before leaving it 
members of the political opposition in hungary say up to 400 east 
germans have gone underground fearing persecution if they go home 
west germany closed its east berlin mission aug 8 after 131 east 
germans seeking guarantees of passage to west germany sought refuge 
inside 
hanns schumacher spokesman for the foreign ministry in bonn 
