<TEXT>
key dates in the life of pw 
botha 
jan 12 1916 botha is born on a farm in the orange free state 
may 1 1936 he quits university to take a job as an organizer 
for the national party in the cape province 
19391940 botha helps form cape province branch of the 
ossewabrandwag oxwagon fire guard a group sympathetic to the 
nazis and opposed south africa joining the allied side in world war 
ii he was threatened with internment but turns against the 
ossewabrandwag when it split with national party leaders 
march 13 1943 botha marries elize rossouw 
may 26 1948 botha becomes a member of parliament from george 
in cape province as his national party comes to power 
october 1958 botha is appointed deputy minister of the 
interior his duties include close involvement with administering 
the group areas act which segregates residential and business areas 
by race 
aug 2 1961 he becomes a cabinet minister in charge of 
community development and colored mixedrace affairs 
april 5 1966 he becomes minister of defense and is 
instrumental in making south africa nearly selfsufficient in arms 
despite a united nations arms embargo 
1966 he is elected leader of the national party in cape 
province one of four powerful provincial leadership posts from 
which party leaders are chosen 
sept 28 1978 botha becomes national party leader and prime 
minister following the resignation of bj vorster 
1979 botha becomes first national leader to visit a black 
township soweto 
1982 the national party rightwing breaks away forming the 
conservative party in response to bothas plans to include indians 
and people of mixedrace in parliament in separate chambers botha 
met with zambian president kenneth kaunda 
1984 the new constitution is adopted creating the 
threechambered parliament that excludes the black majority and 
changes bothas title from prime minister to president with 
wideranging powers botha tours europe and declares apartheid is 
dead 
june 12 1986 botha declares a national emergency to subdue the 
unrest and nationwide violence that erupted in the black communities 
in response to the new constitution 
jan 18 1989 botha suffers a stroke and subsequently gives up 
leadership of the national party 
march 1989 under pressure from party leaders he agrees to 
resign from the presidency following sept 6 parliamentary elections 
july 5 1989 botha invites imprisoned african national congress 
leader nelson mandela to his official cape town residence for a 
conversation 
aug 14 1989 botha announces his resignation 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

