land before time mca home video vhsbeta 2495 rated g 
 
the land before time is one of the few animated childrens 
features of recent years that can hold a candle to the old walt 
disney classics no surprise that its primarily the creation of don 
bluth who worked for disney before he left to start his own company 
the film tells the simple story of littlefoot a lovable baby 
brontosaurus who must make his way from his homeland which is 
being wracked by earthquakes and volcanoes to a green oasis known 
as the great valley 
along the way littlefoot is separated from his grandparents 
sees his mother killed fights off the villainous sharptooth and 
makes friends with other young creatures of varying shapes and 
species 
bluth and his coproducers john pomeroy and gary goldman manage 
to make these primordial characters appealing without being 
sickeningly cute the animation is inventive and the dramatic scenes 
like the big earthquake or sharptooths attack extremely vivid 
very young children may be frightened by these parts and upset by 
the mothers death but aside from that caution this is that rare 
film that can honestly be recommended for viewers of all ages it 
even holds up under repeated watching 
by mike silverman associated press writer 
