world war ii pilot robert morgan who 
flew the renowned american b17 flying fortress bomber called the 
memphis belle is pleased matthew modine is playing a character 
based on him in a new movie but he thinks the actor has one thing 
to learn 
ive got to get matthew a little bit more egotistical morgan 
chuckled referring to the star of memphis belle which retraces 
the 25th and last mission in 1943 of that b17 and the 10 men who 
flew it 
the movie budgeted at 206 million began its 10week shoot in 
britain july 17 modine the 30yearold star of full metal 
jacket and birdy costars with eric stoltz mask some 
kind of wonderful who is the radio operator and db sweeney 
eight men out as the navigator 
john lithgow the original star of m butterfly on broadway 
plays the public relations officer who views the memphis belle 
mission as a chance to boost both war bond sales and sagging morale 
michael catonjones the glaswegian filmmaker who made 
scandal directs from a screenplay by monte merrick the film is 
coproduced by catherine wyler daughter of the movie director 
william wyler and david puttnam the british producer of chariots 
of fire and the mission 
memphis belle is due for release in the united states in 
september 1990 and in britain one month later 
it is puttnams first movie project since he finished a 
muchpublicized hollywood spell as chairman and chief executive of 
columbia pictures two years ago and the 48yearold puttnam hopes 
it will counter films such as the 1986 blockbuster top gun 
which he said glorified air combat 
i couldnt work out what that film was about other than men 
zooming around the skies he said in an interview on the set at an 
abandoned royal air force base in binbrook lincolnshire 180 miles 
northeast of london i was wondering if it was possible to take 
the technical qualities of top gun and use them in a dramatic film 
about human beings 
puttnam said he was inspired by a 1944 documentary by william 
wyler about the memphis belle wyler flew in the bomber five times 
to get the footage 
that was unashamedly a propaganda film made for a job but it 
did its job rather well said puttnam we all agreed it was the 
basis for a really good film 
memphis belle relates 24 hours before the bombers final 
mission a successful raid over bremen in northwest germany the 
aircraft was then brought back to the united states where the same 
10member crew flew it across the country as a propaganda exercise 
in may 1987 it was restored and is now on display in memphis 
in the film five b17s were used for the flying sequences one 
crashed during filming july 25 injuring two technicians none of 
the stars was aboard 
the characters in the movie are fictionalized versions of the 
original crew eight of whom are still alive and were flown to the 
lincolnshire location to help promote the movie 
eugene adkins an original memphis belle gunner now living in 
johnson city tenn said the onset visit was like christmas to 
us i never dreamed it would ever happen again 
robert hansen the crews original radio operator said eric 
stoltzs equivalent character in the movie undergoes a more 
difficult ordeal than hansen did in the actual mission 
they have a tough time bringing eric through said hansen 
who lives in mesa ariz by contrast hansen said he was a zigger 
and a zagger when they were shooting at me i zigged and when the 
bullets went by i zagged so they didnt hit me 
stoltz said he was enjoying the challenge 
this is a completely new arena for me which is what i really 
enjoy about being an actor it gives me a chance to playact said 
the 27yearold actor a tony nominee for his performance last 
season in the lincoln center revival of thornton wilders our 
town 
it gives me a chance to be in the military which is something 
i would never do in reality said stoltz who spent what he called 
an egobashing week with the rest of the cast at a training camp 
in dartmoor in southern england 
stoltz said the enduring rapport of the real memphis belle 
veterans was an inspiration its fun to see a group of men still 
glad to be alive still loving life and theyre 70 
