<TEXT>
teachers and school administrators got their 
first look monday at turner broadcasting system incs daily news 
show for use in the classroom a commercialfree alternative to the 
sponsored news program that whittle communications plans to launch 
next spring 
turner is calling its program cnn newsroom and it will be carried 
weekdays at 345 am edt on cable news network 
the predawn telecast is designed to enable teachers to tape the 
program and review it to see if all or part could be used in class 
later that day 
the program was launched well before the new school year begins 
to give teachers and administrators a chance to determine if it fits 
with their lesson plans turner also gets a jump of several months 
on whittles adsupported channel one news program that begins 
nationally in march 
with the notable exception of commercials the first 15minute 
edition of cnn newsroom resembled the 12minute channel one programs 
that whittle communications tested over a sevenweek period in six 
schools last spring 
both programs are anchored by a youthful and demographically 
balanced team the cnn newsroom anchors are cassandra henderson and 
brian todd turner broadcasting employees selected from a group of 
more than 250 applicants 
the programs open with news headlines contain filmed news 
footage make liberal use of maps and carry several feature stories 
chosen and developed to appeal to teenagers 
cnn newsroom had an expanded feature on the career of rep mickey 
leland the texas democrat who was killed in an airplane crash in 
ethiopia 
it also had a feature on a georgia high school teacher who gives 
his students practical experience in using the english language by 
having them research write and edit stories for a folklore magazine 
he publishes 
and it had a feature on chinese students who have found they must 
sit through lessons taught by the army in the aftermath of the 
bloody suppression of a student uprising this summer in beijing 
during its test run earlier this year channel one had features 
on the life of civil rights leader martin luther king jr and series 
that dealt with the environment and life in russia for teenagers 
the services are delivered differently 
cnn newsroom arrives by cable or is taped off television at home 
while channel one is delivered by satellite 
atlantabased turner said it has endorsements or pledges of 
support from cable operators representing nearly 50 percent of the 
cable television hosueholds in the united states to deliver the 
program to schools 
turner is paying the entire bill for producing the show and 
providing a teachers guide by electronic mail to help in using the 
program in class 
whittle based in knoxville tenn is providing both the program 
and delivery by using advertising revenue 
whittle said only a fraction of the nations classrooms are 
individually equipped with tv sets and that without them teachers 
are unable to make the best use possible of the daily news service 
and other television programs 
channel one schools get an average of 50000 in video hardware 
including tv sets videocassette recorders and satellite dishes in 
exchange for allowing whittle to sell two minutes of commercials in 
each 12minute news program to advertisers during the test 
companies pitched candy bars deodorant and jeans to the 
toughtoreach teen audience 
several national education groups have blasted whittle for taking 
unfair advantage of students who are required to be in school and 
may find it difficult to avoid the commercials 
new york education officials have prohibited public schools in 
that state from subscribing to channel one and the top educational 
officer in california has said any school in his state that takes it 
risks losing state aid 
nonetheless whittle hopes to sign up 8000 schools for channel 
one by the start of the 199091 school year turner expects teachers 
in about 1000 schools will use cnn newsroom when school starts in 
the next few weeks 
