us food and drug administrations ruling against nonprescription 
products that claim to promote hair growth or prevent hair loss 
the headline for the ad reads the good news is theres one 
product thats proven to grow hair rogaine 
the ads also will appear in many national magazines beginning 
next week 
on july 7 the fda said that none of the manufacturers of the 
dozens of nonprescription creams and lotions on the market has 
shown that any of those products work 
when the ban goes into effect in january manufacturers of any 
nonprescription drugs claiming to prevent baldness or grow hair 
will have to provide proof that it is safe and effective before it 
can be put on the market 
the agency will remove the products from the market on a 
casebycase basis if their distributors continue to make such 
claims without proof 
upjohn estimates american men spend more than 200 million each 
year on such unproven hairloss products 
rogaine a 2 percent minoxidil solution is the only fdaapproved 
hair loss treatment it has been on the market since last september 
what this does is enable us to more directly refer to rogaine 
and at the same time use the fda ruling to differentiate rogaine 
from all the other wouldbe treatments upjohn spokesman tr reid 
said 
financial analysts who have been disappointed with rogaine 
sales have blamed part of the products lackluster performance on 
ambiguous advertising in the past upjohn hasnt used the name of 
the product in its ads because the fda requires full disclosure of 
possible side effects 
the ads have used only the company name and advised balding men 
to see their doctors if they are concerned about hair loss 
the latest ads list the products possible side effects such as 
itching of the scalp as well as its effectiveness the topical 
solution has been shown in testing to grow hair in about 39 percent 
of young men who are in the early stages of balding 
us food and drug administration rules prohibit companies from 
advertising brand names of prescription drugs unless the ads also 
list possible side effects and any warnings about use of the drug 
the ads which feature a tollfree number for more information 
also offers a 10 certificate as an incentive to visit your 
doctor 
the drug costs about 60 for a onemonth supply 
the ads also say that 2 million men have tried rogaine upjohn 
which doesnt release sales of individual products said the 
products performance continues to climb 
</TEXT>
